’Щ@1de7b8a7d6fb809f04f353970bee3c4b85f1535983ce526e2307941dd6959298ЪsTitle: title: bits ror
Path: Examples
Content:
rotate right a number with 2 bits
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 17 | bits ror 2
68

```
rotate right a list of numbers of two bytes
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [15 33 92] | bits ror 2 --number-bytes 2
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚ 49155 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚ 16392 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚    23 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
rotate right binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ff bb 03] | bits ror 10
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   c0 ff ee                                             Г—Г—Г—


```
